-Hey. -Hey, what's up?
-嘿 -怎么样啊？

166
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:12,650
I'm making something for Joey. Can I raid your fridge?
我在替乔伊弄点东西 可以搜一下你的冰箱吗？

167
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,330
Have at it.
请便

168
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:19,800
All right. Turkey? That won't work.
好，火鸡肉？没有用

169
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:22,500
Cheese? That won't work.
起司？没有用

170
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:26,210
Olive loaf? I hope that won't work.
橄榄面包，希望这没用

171
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,010
Are you making him a sandwich?
你在替他做三明治吗？

172
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:33,750
No, it's more like a wrap.
不，比较像是鸡肉卷

173
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:38,320
Okay, so I'm gonna go, guys.
好，我要走了

174
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:43,120
So you can get back to deciding on what to get me for a present!
你们可以继续讨论 要送我什么礼物！

175
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:48,660
We have to get her a present?
我们要送她礼物？

176
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,530
Okay, but look. Look at what I got.
好吧，看我拿到什么

177
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:56,040
It's her address book. We have a guest list.
她的通讯录 我们的宾客名单

178
00:11:57,780 --> 00:12:01,080
You're amazing. Did you pull that out of her purse?
你好厉害，你从她皮包拿的？

179
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:04,880
Uh-huh. And a little seed money for the party.
嗯，还有派对的种子钱

180
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:15,230
Cassie?
凯西？

181
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,020
Hey, Ross!
罗斯！

182
00:12:18,770 --> 00:12:21,170
It's been so long!
好久不见！

183
00:12:21,970 --> 00:12:23,370
Last time I saw you...
上一次我看到你时…

184
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:27,370
you were setting up your tent in line for Return of the Jedi.
你正搭着帐篷 等待绝地武士的归来

185
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:33,670
So you did see me that day. Because it seemed like you didn't.
所以那天你有看到我 看起来像没看到的样子

187
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:38,540
-Yeah, sorry about that. -It's okay. Come on in.
-对不起 -没关系，请进

188
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:42,750
Thanks for letting me stay here. Monica's place was nice.
谢谢你让我住在这儿 摩妮卡那儿不错

189
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:46,390
But her fiance sure stares a lot.
但她的未婚夫一直瞪着人看

190
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:11,810
Oh, my God! You do a great Chandler!
我的天！你学钱德学得真像！

191
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:18,460
I have a knack for impressions.
我很会做表情的

192
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:21,750
Maybe after we get re-acquainted you could do me.
等我们熟一点 你也可以学我

193
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,360
Yeah. No!
好，不！

194
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:36,770
How you doing on that...
你的…

195
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:38,470
hot dog?
热狗好吃吗？

196
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:43,680
-I'm all done. -Thank God.
-我吃完了 -感谢上帝

197
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:51,220
The last time we hung out was when our parents rented that beach house.
上次见面是我们父母 租下海边小屋那时

198
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:56,330
Remember the time I pinned you down and tickled you until you cried?
记得我按住你 搔你痒直到你哭了？

199
00:13:58,170 --> 00:14:01,190
We're probably too old to do that now.
我们现在大了，不能这么做了

200
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:08,310
I'll always remember that summer. It's when I got all these freckles.
我一直都记得那个夏天 我就是那时长了这些雀斑的

201
00:14:10,980 --> 00:14:13,970
I'll always remember that summer...
我一直都记得那个夏天…

202
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:17,880
because that's when I realized that we are related.
因为那时我才知道我们是亲戚

203
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,980
It took you that long to figure it out?
你花了那么久才发现？

204
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:22,520
I'm a little slow.
我是有点反应迟缓

205
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,150
Just as our children would be.
就如我们的孩子也可能会这样子

206
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,360
-Hi. -Hi.
-嗨 -嗨

207
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:38,760
How are you? Good. Hi. Thanks for coming.
你好吗？好，嗨 谢谢大家来

208
00:14:39,010 --> 00:14:41,200
Thank you. So nice to see you.
谢谢，很高兴看到你

209
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:44,210
-No, thanks. -Okay. Hey, Rach?
-不，谢谢 -好，瑞秋？

210
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:47,010
-Yeah? -Who the hell are all these people?
-是？ -这些是什么人啊？

211
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:50,680
I don't know. I called everybody in her book.
我不知道 我打给她本子里的每一个人

212
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:54,790
These are the ones that could show up on 24 hours' notice.
这些是在24小时内通知还能来的

213
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:58,150
There's a word for people like that: Losers.
有另一个字来形容这种人：输家

214
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:03,220
Hi, I'm Rachel. This is Phoebe. I'm the maid of honor.
我是瑞秋，这是菲比 我是伴娘

215
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:07,060
-How do you know Monica? -I was her accountant four years ago.
-你怎么认识摩妮卡的？ -我是她四年前的会计师

216
00:15:07,370 --> 00:15:12,470
I'm interested to find out who's been doing her taxes the last four years.
我很想知道 这过去四年是谁替她报税

217
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,070
That's great.
很好

218
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:20,210
-When is Monica supposed to get here? -I don't know.
-摩妮卡何时会到？ -我不知道

219
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:22,880
Excuse us.
借一步说话

220
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:27,990
-You didn't tell her? -You were supposed to.
-你没告诉她？ -你该通知她的

221
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:31,880
You were supposed to tell her to come! I was bringing the cake!
是你该通知她来的！ 我要带蛋糕！

222
00:15:32,090 --> 00:15:36,220
-Fine, I'll go call her. -And please tell her to bring a cake!
-好，我打电话给她 -要她带蛋糕来！

223
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:47,400
We have a lot of options. A number of prototypes for you to try on.
我们有很多选择 有几个雏型可以试穿

224
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:49,630
Those look great.
看起来很好

225
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:54,580
Okay, this one's a mushroom cap. This one is made of bologna.
这个有磨菇做的头 这个是意大利香肠做的

226
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:57,510
-The toothpicks? -Just until the glue dries.
-牙签？ -只是撑着等胶水干掉

227
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:58,950
Thank God.
感谢上帝

228
00:16:00,650 --> 00:16:03,420
These are more realistic, but perishable.
这些比较逼真，但会腐烂

229
00:16:04,290 --> 00:16:07,520
Over here, we have pink suede, which is nice.
这儿，粉红色的鞣皮，很不错

230
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,160
But if it gets wet, it'll shrink.
但湿了会缩水

231
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:12,920
Maybe we'll just take that one away.
把这个拿走好了

232
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:18,830
I also did a little something in fur, but that's really just for me.
我也做了一个毛的 不过那是给我自己的

233
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:26,010
Why don't you try these on? We'll get a better idea of what works.
不如你去试试这些？ 我们就知道哪些有用

234
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,770
Thanks, you are such a good friend. And this is so weird.
谢谢，你真是位好朋友 这真是奇怪透顶

235
00:16:37,790 --> 00:16:39,660
-Toothpick? -Yeah.
-牙签的？ -是

236
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,990
-What are you trying now? -The Fruit Roll-up.
-你现在在试那个？ -水果卷

237
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:46,060
-And? -Delicious.
-然后呢？ -很好吃

238
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:52,070
Wait a minute. Wait a minute. We have a winner!
等一下，等一下 冠军出线了！

239
00:16:52,310 --> 00:16:53,900
What? Which one?
怎样？哪一个？

240
00:16:54,910 --> 00:16:58,370
The Silly Putty. Not so silly anymore!
笨油灰不再那么笨了！

241
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:12,890
She's your cousin. She's your cousin.
她是你表妹 她是你表妹

242
00:17:13,590 --> 00:17:19,030
If she knew what was going on in your head, she'd think you were sick.
如果她知道你脑袋里在想什么 她会以为你有病

243
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:29,030
Or would she? Let's back up for a second.
她会吗？ 倒转一下

244
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:34,180
She was the one who suggested opening a bottle of wine.
是她提议开红酒的

245
00:17:34,380 --> 00:17:37,370
She was the one who turned down the lights.
是她把灯光调暗的

246
00:17:37,580 --> 00:17:41,710
She was the one that wanted to rent Logan's Run...
是她要租《二十三世纪大逃亡》的…

247
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:44,410
the sexiest movie ever.
有史以来最性感的电影

248
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,860
I know that look.
我知道这眼神

249
00:17:50,060 --> 00:17:54,400
Forget it. I want it. She wants it.
不管了，我想要，她想要

250
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,130
I'm going in.
我要行动了

251
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,240
What the hell are you doing?
你在干什么？

252
00:18:09,620 --> 00:18:11,580
Say something clever.
说点机智的

253
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,580
Okay, doesn't have to be clever.
好吧，不必机智的

254
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:19,920
Just has to be words. Say some words.
只要说点什么，说话

255
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:23,890
Any words will do.
什么话都好

256
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:28,130
Oh, my God, this is the longest...
我的天，这是有史以来…

257
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:32,930
that anyone has not talked ever!
最长的沉默！

258
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:38,770
There is nothing you could say to make this worse...
说什么都不可能让情形更糟…

259
00:18:38,980 --> 00:18:40,780
so just say something!
说点什么！

260
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:46,610
I haven't had sex in a very long time.
我很久没做爱了

261
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:53,160
Yeah, you really shouldn't have said anything.
你真的不该说话的

262
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,990
Phoebe? Rachel? It's Monica.
菲比？瑞秋？是摩妮卡

263
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:02,500
I wonder what you could possibly need me for on such short notice?
什么事这么急着找我来呢？

264
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:11,010
-Oh, Monica. We are so sorry. -For what?
-摩妮卡，我们很抱歉 -为什么？

265
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:14,980
First, for forgetting to throw you a bridal shower.
第一，忘了替你办告别单身女子派对

266
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:17,650
Then, forgetting to invite you to it.
然后忘了邀请你

267
00:19:20,190 --> 00:19:21,520
You already had it?
你们已经办完了？

268
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:25,180
We called everyone in your phone book. A bunch of people came.
我们打电话给你通讯录里每一个人 来了很多人

269
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:28,620
It took us so long to get you here that they had to leave.
但花了太多时间找到你 客人都走了

270
00:19:29,530 --> 00:19:33,730
We wanted to throw you a big surprise and a great shower.
我们想给你一个大惊喜 替你办一个大的告别单身女子派对

271
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:35,830
Now you don't have either.
现在两个都没了

272
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:37,470
We ruined everything.
我们毁了一切

273
00:19:37,670 --> 00:19:42,440
No, wait a minute, that's not true. What you did was really sweet.
不，等一下，没有毁了一切 你们真的很好心

274
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:46,310
-It kind of works out for the best. -What do you mean?
-其实这样子最好 -什么意思？

275
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:50,880
Now I get to spend my shower with the only people I really love.
现在我可以和我真正喜欢的人 一起共渡我的告别单身女子派对

276
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:55,950
I get all those presents without talking to people I don't even like!
我收了所有的礼物 而不必和我不喜欢的人说话！

277
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:03,820
-Surprise. -Surprise, Monica.
-惊喜 -惊喜，摩妮卡

278
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:14,000
What's cool is, the character is from Naples, right?
最酷的是，这个角色是从尼泊尔来的

279
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:16,570
My whole family's from Naples.
我全家都是从尼泊尔来的

280
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:21,970
That's great. Okay. I've heard everything I need to hear...
太好了，我听得差不多了…

281
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:24,610
We just need to, uh...
我们只需要…

282
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:26,240
Leslie?
莱斯莉？

283
00:20:26,820 --> 00:20:31,120
-Joey, this is the awkward part. -Hey, right. Not a problem.
-乔伊，这有点怪怪的 -是，没有问题

284
00:20:31,390 --> 00:20:33,620
I totally understand you need to...
我完全了解…

285
00:20:33,890 --> 00:20:37,590
make sure I don't have any horrible scars or tattoos.
你们需要能确定 我没有可怕的疤痕或刺青

286
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,230
Don't you worry.
不用担心

287
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,370
I have nothing to hide.
我没什么要隐藏的

288
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:46,570
So, there you go. That's me.
这儿，这就是我

289
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:49,140
One hundred-percent natural.
百分之百纯天然

290
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:08,420
I tell you, that has never happened before.
这从来没发生过

291
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,930
Cassie, are you finding everything okay?
凯西，一切都还好吗？

292
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,930
Yeah. Thanks for letting me stay here.
是，谢谢你让我住这儿

293
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:22,370
Oh, it's no problem.
没问题

294
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:41,580
What?
怎么？

295
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:44,760
Say something. Say anything.
说话，随便说什么

296
00:21:45,230 --> 00:21:47,890
Ask her out! She's not your cousin!
约她出去！她不是你表妹！

297
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000


298
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
